{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7anxbCEbt6giXKc3Yn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Both tests pass.\n\n**The bug** (`src/money.js`): the spec says the discount applies to the order subtotal and is rounded to the nearest cent **once**. The code instead rounded each line's discounted amount individually, then summed those. That per-line rounding drifts upward.\n\n**The customer's case**: two $5.00 lines at 10.1% off should be `1000 × 0.899 = 899` → **$8.99**. The old code rounded each line separately: `round(500 × 0.899) = 450` twice → `900` → **$9.00**, exactly the one-cent overcharge billing saw.\n\n**The fix**: sum the raw subtotal in integer cents first, apply the discount, and round the result a single time — matching the documented contract. I also added a regression test that reproduces the $8.99/$9.00 discrepancy.\n\n`src/report.js` has a `// TODO: rounding here is sketchy?` comment, but its `(cents / 100).toFixed(2)` is correct once the cents value is right, so I left it alone."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":446,"cache_read_input_tokens":24323,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":446},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d800c5a-e135-41ec-b720-6b5671b2a0b3","uuid":"d97fc286-0fac-4015-afa3-0b168f99e943","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:42:25.414Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7amPLMLaCqgsUmv4yf"}
